Chicken a la King

- Meat from about 1/2 a medium cooked chicken
- 2 shallots
- 1 bell pepper
Cube chicken meat, mince shallots, dice pepper


- 6 Tbsp butter
- 1/2 lb sliced mushrooms
Slice mushrooms if necessary
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add mushrooms, bell pepper, and some salt.
Saute until mushrooms just start to brown, about 9 minutes.

Add shallots and cook until just soft, about 3 minutes.

- 2/3 cup flour
Reduce heat to medium, stir in flour to coat mushrooms and cook until rawness is cooked out of flour, about 4 minutes.


- 1/4 cup dry sherry or white wine
- 4 cups chicken stock
Deglaze with sherry.
Add stock a little at a time, stirring to mix evenly before adding more.

Bring just to boil, then reduce heat and simmer for about 10 minutes until thickened.

- 1 pinch nutmeg
- 1 pinch cayenne
- 3/4 tsp dried thyme leaves
- 1 tsp dried parsley
- 1/3 cup heavy cream
Add nutmeg, cayenne, thyme, parsley and cream and mix evenly. Add chicken, then cook until chicken is heated through. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

